                  <msItem class="#sermones" n="1" xml:id="MS_Bodl_402-item1">
                     <locus>(fol. 1) </locus>
                     <title key="work_14583" type="desc">Sermons</title>
                     <note>453 sermons or short discourses, partly at least
                        on the Sunday Gospels (Evangelia Dominicalia).</note>
                     <note type="index">With two indexes of subjects
                        to the 'materie in hoc opere contente', the first to sermons 1-367, the
                        second supplementary, including an added portion, sermons 368-453: the first
                        is 'tabula composita per manum iohannis de Riuuilla (fol. 312v: Wallenstadt
                        in Switzerland?), and the second is ascribed in two hexameters to
                        'Io-han-nes'</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="MS_Bodl_402-item2">
